festival.introText:
As the longest running festival in Tisno, the idyllic hideaway SunceBeat is nestled away with its own glittering bay and pine-shaded site - there’s no better place for a week of sun-kissed and star-speckled escapism by day and night.

Each year we bring together many of the world’s leading DJs and producers who rub shoulders with the burgeoning next generation of talent. And this is only part of SunceBeat’s magic - it’s really a holiday and festival blended as one, set in a beautiful landscape which is an escape from reality and responsibility.

Born in 2010, SunceBeat continues to innovate on the beautiful Dalmatian coast. We were the first to bring deep house titan Larry Heard to Tisno, the first to invite Berlin powerhouse Prosumer to spin, and the first Croatian festival to secure a date with the semi-mythical icon DJ Harvey. The trend continues with the likes of LNTG, Black Coffee, MCDE, Hunee and Antal, Jeremy Underground and first to bring Kerri Chandler & Louie Vega over, plus the only festival yet to bring DJ Jazzy Jeff to The Garden Resort in Tisno. We are proud of our track record with debutants, including for 2022 alone MYD, Colleen ‘Cosmo’ Murphy, Kings of Tomorrow Ft Julie McKnight, Arielle Free, Ultra Nate, Ash Lauryn, Demuja, Emmaculate, Holly Lester and many more with headliners including The Blessed Madonna, David Morales and Fred Everything.

Live artists who have performed include The Brand New Heavies, Roy Ayres, Lonnie Liston Smith and Grammy Award Winner Gregory Porter. We remain committed to curating a bold and diverse line-up each summer representative of our vision to join the dots between the best of the past and the future innovators across myriad genres.

From the stunning main stage to water-side Beach Bar and from the pumping Olive Grove to the simply jaw-dropping open-air club Barbarella’s, to the wild boat parties on the legendary vessels The Argonaughty and The Arbiana, SunceBeat is always abundant with music and dancing with friends old and new.

reviews.title: Review of Suncebeat 10

reviews.title: Review of Suncebeat 9
reviews.body: Absolutely brilliant!  Have previously been to Electric Elephant & Love International at the same location, which were both great, but the music could sometimes be hit or miss for my tastes (I like disco & deep house).  However, the music at Suncebeat was spot on every day\night.  The farewell boat & night at the beach stage was one of the best nights I have ever had!

reviews.title: Review of Suncebeat 9
reviews.body: Great event. poor selection of lager, a branded alternative to the homebrew is required.

faqs.question: How do I get to Suncebeat Festival?
faqs.answer:
Getting there by Car - Car hire in Tisno is not necessary as the festival site is just a short walk from the town. But if you do want to explore more of the country then we can recommend Budget Car Rental and Uni Rent.

 

Getting There By Air - Tisno is a small Dalmatian town on the island of Murter, situated half on the island, half on the mainland, and linked with 20m bascule-bridge. It is located 45km south of Zadar airport and 65km north of Split airport so is ideally situated for those of you flying in. We’ll be listing the available flight options from across Europe as soon as they are released by the airline companies.

 

Airport Transfers

Our friends at Shuttle Tours offer discount coach transfers for from most Croatian airports to the festival site. Visit their website here to check latest prices and availability.

faqs.question: Does Suncebeat have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: Onsite accommodation options are available as a separate booking through the Suncebeat website including bell tents, mobile homes and apartments.

faqs.question: disabled access information
faqs.answer: for information on disabled access at Suncebeat Festival please contact damo@tandempr.co.uk

faqs.question: Where is Suncebeat?
faqs.answer: Suncebeat takes place at The Garden Tisno in Croatia.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: Payment Plan tickets are not currently available through Skiddle however there are options for group bookings.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately, we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these

circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Suncebeat?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Suncebeat.

faqs.question: Does Suncebeat have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: SunceBeat is a child-friendly event we love having the kids at the party all children under 16 go free of charge.
